caption: Beautiful upscale classy modern contemporary Italian cuisine... exceptional service! Make a reservation for the crowded weekends, quieter during the week.

So, the food was alright. Nothing really truly outstanding. However, this is easily the best dining experiences I’ve ever received in my life. Our waiter, a soon to be sommelier, was phenomenal. He suggested the perfect bottle for me and was extremely knowledgeable and passionate about his craft the entire night. I would come back time and time again just for him!

Fantastic vibe, excellent food, generous portions, superb wine choices. You can't beat house-made fresh pasta! The wine pairings were perfect with each course. Each dish is expertly plated and crafted like a work of art.

I’ve honestly had better tasting meals at Carrabba’s for a lot cheaper. I got rockfish and it was so grossly over cooked. The apps and pasta dishes are uninspired, it’s a joke of an Italian restaurant. Go to Little Italy if you want a good Italian dish in Baltimore, save yourself the money and disappointment.
Awesome....

We somehow always end up eating a second dinner here when stopping by for a glass of wine.. The lamb taggliette and squid ink spaghetti are amazing. Always prepared with care. Also, try the biscotti with ceremony coffee espresso for dessert.

One of my preferred locations for delicious italian food. Do yourself a favor and try this place. The service was very friendly and attentive. This place has a good atmosphere. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I liked.
italian food and the scene at this location is super good. I was so stuffed. Service is typically good. I can see why they have so many good reviews.

The chef was very pleasant and explained each piece to us as he handed it to us and answered any questions we had. This is also a BYOB restaurant so don't forget to bring a bottle of sake!! They also take precautions very seriously for indoor dining.
This was a special dinner at this lovely restaurant.
Simply amazing! Some of the best food I have ever tried.
We were two couples and all were pleased with service and meals. Very nice atmosphere and the food is expertly prepared.Highly recommended!!

It was so good the first night, we had to come back the next night. The salumi offered was top notch (definitely order the norcino) and the pastas very good. Wish we lived closer!  I feel like I owe all these people dinner at my house now -- and your money is going to help a city and its people at a hard time. If you're looking at this and thinking about going, just do it.
Phenomenal food and excellent service. Our server Parrish made excellent food and wine recommendations. So many amazing things to try on the menu. A true gem of Baltimore’s dining scene.
Excellent. Love the food. Staff was great.

Went in with my wife for our first anniversary on 11/14. Start to finish, this was an exceptional experience. Our server was a true professional and helped us understand an extensive wine list with some unfamiliar terms (for me, a novice). He did not guide us wrong. We ordered off the salami menu, got two pastas, and shared a main dish. This was a perfect amount of food. The tagliatelli dish with lamb was the highlight for me. Just awesome down to the last detail. For dessert, our server brought us a Panna cotta - which i didn't expect to enjoy - but it was fantastic!! A great way to close out a meal (and settle the stomach). I don't write a ton of reviews, but this restaurant left an impression!.. and took every precaution for covid which is greatly appreciated. Highly recommend. Enjoy.
Italian food, mmm, super good. Do not leave if it's busy, it is worth it. Will surely make a return trip.

Adding to everything others have said, first visit last night made us staunch supporters. Prix fixe with the wine paring was fantastic with a huge selection to fill your card. Given COVID restrictions tables far apart & comfortable conversation was free & easy. Service was top notch, a perfect dress up date night for us. Again kudos to the chef & staff!

Our waiter was incredible! We opted for the chef tasting and the food was just okay. Not what I expected from such a prominent restaurant. I've also seen a few other reviews about the host being unpleasant and I 100% agree. We overheard him changing our table to a different room because we weren't dressed up to par for him apparently. It put a negative spin on our anniversary dinner.

This is a great place, the food was delicious and so were the drinks. The service is impeccable, staff very knowledgeable. We sat in the outdoor patio this time and really enjoyed it. Highly recommend this restaurant!
Lovely restaurant for a special occasion. Great food, atmosphere.
Italian food and the feeling at this place is excellent. Fast, efficient, and courteous service.
Very good atmosphere  really cool staff was polite food and drinks was definitely good

5 stars. Wonderful experience.  My wife and I dined in for the first time since COVID.  What a way to break quarantine.  Otherworldly Bronzino Crudo, Venison, Rabbit, Squid ink pasta, cured meats, cheeses, etc.  A wine menu to die for to boot.

The food was perfect, except for the tiramisu. It was severely over coated that I tapped the excess on to the plate. The good part of my experience is the wine recommended matched perfectly to the kind of palate I was looking for. The negative part.....service started out so slow my guests thought we were a "pick up" table aka table in an area not assigned to a server. When I called in my reservation I said we are celebrating a birthday, the server was not informed. For fine dining I expected better steps of service.
Pretentious very expensive doesn't even carry beer spent $200 for two people will not be returning

This place was Northern Italy, and the 3 for $62 was amazing splurg on the wine of choice cuz 3oz wine pairing isn't a suggestion you wanna take advantage of. Their wine selection is phenomenal and worth the cost.
Excellent food, excellent selection of wines, excellent hospitality, great ambiance.
Worth the price!

Celebrated our 11th Anniversary there last night (9/5/20). We always carefully choose where we eat each year and this year was no different. The antipastas were delicious. My wife had the squid ink pasta and I had my favorite gnocchi. Both were outstanding. For our third choice my wife had the recommended Tbone steak and I had the pan seared Venison. Both cooked to perfection. I loved the wine reduction sauce with my venison and swiss shard. I don't like shard but loved it tonight.  Tonight's front expertise was outstanding as well. Parrish recommended a Italian Cab that was so outstanding we asked where we can buy another for our own collection.  Highly recommend and will return again in the future.  Delaneys
My fav location for italian food. i love this place always quality food & service. had a friend come into town and she asked me to take her here again.
Excellent food and service. Great social justice consciences during COVID-19 pandemic!
One of my fav places for italian food. Do yourself a favor and give this place a try. It has a good atmosphere. Food and atmosphere reminds me of Atlanta.
A preferred spot for delicious Italian food. very filling. there was quick, helpful, and friendly service. this place has a cool design.
Good place for delicious italian food. Fell in love with this place from the 1st taste. Service treated us so kindly. Prices were average for the menu.
Food was delicious
Excellent.  Parish was phenomenal.
Everything excellent

Great host, waitstaff and valet. Rude manager or whoever he is in suit and tie. Seriously, you should learn how to ask if we are done with our antipasti before taking the plate away. And he was rude when asked about it. Where is your restaurant service etiquette? For that alone if I ever experience that again, I would suggest patrons to to Sotto Sopra instead if I am to have a sit down mean. Heck, I would suggest Di Pasquale's instead, eventhough the setting is casual and closing time is early.

We have been coming to Cinghiale from Howard County since the restaurant opened. We have always enjoyed the food and atmosphere. My friend and I spent Valentines Day here and both had wonderful meals. There was a tasting menu with limited options. Every course of the 4 course meal was superb. This was most likely the best meal we ever enjoyed at Cinghiale and , unlike most suburban restaurants, the exemplary service matched the quality of the food. We won’t wait as long before returning again. Thank you Cinghiale for an exceptional evening.
A bit overpriced, but very delicious
This restaurant has a nice Italian atmosphere. The aromas that circle the restaurant are authentic. An awesome place to have date night or a gathering.

Had a mixed experience. Dined here for dinner with a work group a few weeks ago, interviewing an out of town applicant. Food was excellent. Service was ok but not up to par for this restaurant. The wrong dish was delivered to one of my guests but no one noticed. We had all started eating and they brought out another dish that apparently was the right one. They swapped her meal but without much apology or acknowledgement  of the mistake. It was handled poorly and in my experience if a service driven establishment makes a mistake they typically offer a verbal apology at a minimum. Might try again but with a lower stakes scenario.
Do they give out 6 stars? No? Ok well they should for this place.
The Cinghiale is an amazing experience. The staff was on top of everything. The food was incredible.  Highly recommended!
Wonderful food and service. We will be back.

Great service, food, and wine, plus a great location in harbor east. The dramatic lighting is nice for the younger crowd, but during the time I spent there I saw 4 tables utilize cell phone lights to read the menu, which was equal parts distracting and hilarious.

Wine selection was very good got the Chianti Classico.  Food was smaller portions but very very good. I got the duck breast and it was out of this world.  We also got the grilled calamari and it was superb.

--Solved by Owner-- I purchased a giftcard on Dec 23rd (I knew it was not going to arrive in time by Christmas, so I planned on giving it to my parents a few days later since they were staying in Baltimore until January 12 and wanted them to have a nice meal). It has been 22 days! (1/14/19 today) and I am still waiting for the giftcard to arrive. Sadly, my parents have already left Maryland so they will not get to enjoy their present... I did sent an email last week and I am still waiting for a response. ORDER #1124

I visited during restaurant week and sadly will not be coming back. First of all, it's a very nice, classy atmosphere and the service did not match that. I found myself constantly waiting on water refills, and our drinks (cocktail and wine) came after the first course was already served. I also asked a woman who wasn't our server for salt (because our server was serving a bottle of wine to another table and I didn't want my food getting cold) and she gave me a rude look as if I should be asking my server that. As for the food, I ordered the seafood squid ink spaghetti and while the flavor was delicious, the shellfish was rubbery and I was only given about 5 pieces of it, 2 shrimp and 3 calamari rings. The desserts were pretty lazy as well. I think they used restaurant week as an excuse to cut corners when this is a time to attract new clients.
Nice Italian great pasta in Harbor East. Bar options are solid, menu has something for everyone.
Average taste for the price

This is a fantastic restaurant. We checked it out for restaurant week and everything was amazing. I had the tagliatelle and my husband had the veal. It is relatively fancy but not stuffy. We went in our work clothes and fit right in. Seems like it would be a good place for a special event

Great way to kick off restaurant week! Our server Jimi was great! She made excellent recommendations, and offered expert incite into the Foreman/Wolf experience. Squid ink pasta 👌🏽perfectly prepared, Cinghiale 75 great drink.

Went for Christmas Eve. Based on the lobby and delay in being seated (30 min) with a reservation, it felt like they over booked. Despite being clearly overwhelmed, the service was pretty good. The 3 stars is about the food. I found the butternut squash soup bland and the risotto too salty. Considering it was a holiday, I'd give them another shot on a "regular" night, based on the service.
Classy and elegant

Very enjoyable meal and excellent refined service.  Entree was perfectly prepared, dessert was artfully presented.  Valet service for car, or garage parking around the corner beneath the Four Seasons.

We were there for a special Christmas Eve dinner,  Feast of The Seven Fishes. As with all Foreman/Wolfe restaurants the food was amazing, definitely festive atmosphere, staff perhaps a bit overwhelmed but kept doing a good job. Overall a great experience.
Always an excellent experience at Cinghiale- Great service, amazing food!
Best Italian food in Baltimore!

The food is not good.  My daughter had the lobster risotto which was bland, with tiny flecks of lobster.  My wife had the veal which was just okay.  I had the venison pasta which was bland.  My other daughter had the steak which was again just okay.  No one finished their meals.  We spent over $300 with tip and drinks - for that much I expected way more taste!  I just can't get over how disappointing the food was, yet the place was hopping with customers.  I gave it two stars because the staff was nice, otherwise it would have been 1.  To echo another review on here, I haven't been this disappointed in a meal in a long time.
Our favorite restaurant in Baltimore.

My son and I have been going for the grilled calamari since it opened. The first time I went with my son he was five And now he’s 14. We share October birthdays which we have celebrated a number of them at Cinghiales!
Delicious food . Excellent service

I haven’t even eaten yet and I feel compelled to give them a 5 star. I am here for a birthday dinner and somehow managed to break the bottle of wine I was bringing as a gift. They ran down to their wine store and grabbed a bag and then wrapped a new bottle for me. Outstanding customer service. I can’t wait for the meal.
We had the duck and the NY strip. Both were cooked perfect, and the service was top rate. Highly recommend.

Cinghiale has good ambiance, good collection of drinks , good food and good service. It  was great place to hangout with friends...Its more like regular bar food  and service was good! Will visit again for sure!
Great food

Food, Drink, Service.....A+!!!!! Went there for a rehearsal dinner and honestly it was some of the best food I've ever had in Baltimore! Every dish was full of flavor and the service was beyond comparison!

Celebrating our 28th Anniversary and we chose this place because of the great reviews. They were right on point. We had the 4 Course Meal for $62 a person. We loved the food and ambiance. The portions were plenty and the ending with desserts included was a perfect ending.
Excellent service and quality food!
Amazing atmosphere, excellent service. We did the "prezzo fisso" which was a 4 course experience paired with wine (optional, but highly recommend). Everything was incredible, can't wait to go back!

Disappointing.   We dined here on a Saturday evening.  The supposed attentive waitstaff was unimpressive.  Our server never introduced himself, never brought bread to the table (we finally asked the person who delivered the appetizers), seemed rushed and uninterested, and then shook our hands at the end (yuck).    My lobster dish was quite good but the remaining dishes (two appetizers, risotto with butternut squash,  cavatelli pasta, swordfish) were nothing special and ok at best.  The decor is beautiful but the actual food and experience were very disappointing.
Super quality.   High end feeling worth a reasonable happy hour pricing.
Great value on fine dining here. You expect to pay a lot more than they charge you. Try the duck magret and the pear cake. The veal chop is huge and bland.
The food was delicious! The staff were attentive and quick to reapond
Place was Awesome!
Awesome, great food and service.
Super good food and excellent service.

My wife and I get bizarrely good treatment from this restaurant.  We're treated so well, it confuses me.  We come here decently often, but we're far from regulars.  We normally sit at the bar and chat with the staff, but we normally just get wine and light fare (not even a full meal). I suppose we tip pretty well, but it must be comparatively low to couples who get dinner. So based on all of that, I can't imagine why we get such special treatment.  And then it hit me.  We don't.  That's just how exceptional Tony and his staff are.  You don't normally expect a high end restaurant to have the welcoming ambiance of a corner bar.  But that's the culture here. I can't name many restaurants in the city that get it all right. Cinghiale is one for sure.
Never disappoints! Cindy wolf is a legend 👌
Fantastic restaurant... I really liked this place.

The atmosphere and service were great, especially considering that we were such a large group. The food, however, was not as great. Everyone came away from the meal with the same feeling of meh. As it was restaurant week, it is likely that the menu was "dumbed" down, even still, I'm not sure we'll be going back again.
So good! We didn't realize when we went it was restaurant week. Food was delicious and the branzini was on par with it's sister restaurant Charleston. We will definitely be back soon!

My husband and I tried to prix fixé menu for our anniversary with the wine pairings. Everything was delicious, the wait staff were attentive, but not intrusive. The decor is also lovely. The entire experience was excellent.
I usually do not enjoy fish. But the bronzini and salad were out of control. Italian at it's best here in the inner harbor.
Lovely venue with harbor view. Sophisticated northern Italian menu. Extensive wine list. Excellent service. Kudos to our server Parrish.
Great place, but they ran out of one of the main entres by 6pm on the first night of restaurant week, bit of a bait and switch.
Such a wonderful place, delicious food and drinks, amazing atmosphere.  A must go to in Baltimore!
My favorite restaurant in Baltimore. Never failed to exceed my expectations.
Was not impressed.
username: D I V E R S I F O R M

caption: Everything was perfect, food and service

What an exceptional experience! Arriving at the restaurant being greeted by a friendly valet attended was a great start. Our server Parish (hopefully I spelled it right) was fantastic. Took his time and explained menus, wine pairing (which we did). Just incredible. Chef produced outstanding meals for us that evening. We werena party of 4 (with a birthday guest) and every dish was just incredible and perfectly paired with the right wine. The evening seemed to go by fast, but we did not feel rushed at all. It ended up being 3 hours of elegant dining. It reminded me a lot of Europe. So if you want exceptional food and service and just an incredible dining experience,  come here to Cinghiale.

I just ate here again for about the 6th time because we went elsewhere and had a bad experience with apps and service... so we left to just get something delicious as a last dinner date before baby comes. Oh my goodness this place does not disappoint... and it never has. Cavatelli cooked perfectly with fresh huge morels and fava beans with crunchy garlic and zucchini strips. My husband thought  I would have entree envy over his sausage stuffed parmesan ravioli in sage brown butter but he was mistaken. We got an extra cavatelli to go for the sitter and the service is always amazing. Forever my baltimore go to restaurant.

This place is excellent if you're looking for a little bit more of a fancy meal. The staff are extremely professional but also still down to earth and friendly. Good food and drink selections, plus outdoor seating for a little more casual setting and a separate dining area that's more formal.
It is always spot-on. We had the soft shell crabs light night and they were fabulous! The wine selection is always wonderful and even the bread and olive oil is a diet breaker.

We arrived on time for an 8 o'clock reservation and were seated in an out of the way table by the kitchen doors and an obnoxiously loud group at the end of the bar. We werent given drink or wine menus to browse and couldn't get the attention of any waitstaff. We wanted to request a change in table (the place was half empty) but decided to leave after we couldn't/ weren't able to speak with anyone for 10 minutes unattended from when we were seated.  I'm sure the food is great, but never got past the poor service to try.
Only my second time here. I ate at the bar. It was a very good meal. The risotto was on point. The Scallops were perfect. I will visit again soon.
Superb, informative service.  Food beyond reproach!

The sommelier was superb as was our waitress. That being said the food was not what I expected for this class of restaurant. My group started with the bruschetta as our appetizer; it had no flavour.  Their twist on the dish added goat cheese which was utterly bland.  The tomato and zucchini topping also had no flavour.  A dash of salt, some fresh basil or even some balsamic vinegar would have made a world of difference.  The main dishes were ok.  I will grant that we were a later dinner party, but still plenty of time before closing.  The dish I had, duck ragu if I remember, the noodles were undercooked to the point they were chewy.
Was my best experience to date.  Food was excellent. Try to get their event room if you can as it is carpeted and quieter then the main room.

great food with good vegetarian options. some of then are made with chicken stock so mention if you have any dietary requirements so they can modify. definitely recommend the potato gnocchi with leeks and mushrooms.
Mathew was an amazing host for our first experience.
Chef Hip works his magic with a sublime selection of Italian cheeses. Our meal was wonderful,  the service  exceptional and the desserts memorable. Thank you for a lovely evening!
Best meal I've had in years. Highly recommend the entire menu!
Great food, great wine selection, very good service, Go already!
Great
Great food and wine.
Great Italian Food
Excellent food and attentive staff.
Delicious food, good service, lovely harbor view
Great food, great service, high prices
Our server was very knowledgeable. Service was quick. Food was good but not spectacular. Nice ambience for a romantic setting. Dining area was a bit cold.
Delicious pasta and entrees. Extensive wine list.  Impeccable service.
The pasta dishes are excellent!
Amazing food... we each ordered the 3 course meal ($65) and enjoyed immensely... portions much larger than expected.
Place is beautiful, the service is well but the pasta that we eat has to improve. One of it was too salty, the other was dry and one of it was not cooced well. The desert was ok.

Service was ok, food was way below par and not worth the money. In a group of 10 so dishes were varied and no one was impressed. Meats and cheese pre was great the rest of the meal was not. Haven't been in years and won't be going back anytime soon. If you do don't get the lasagna!
Food and service was amazing.
Excellent food and service for a business dinner with presentation area

Went to dinner with four work colleagues from different home towns while in Baltimore for a conference. The recommendations provided by the staff were on point from appetizers to the sommelier's wine pairings. An absolutely excellent meal.
Pretty damn amazing experience.
Upscale environment serving great food with a reasonable price.

Very good. Made reservations for 7pm on a Saturday. Arrived at 7 and was seated right away. The restaurant has two sides to it as far as seating goes. One side is more of a vibrant atmosphere,  the other is more of a more intimate experience. The service was excellent and the food was the same. Expect to spend around $100 to 200 with tips. Also free valet parking. I cannot tell a lie🎩

I was there when they just started serving dinner. I didn't feel welcomed at all. In fact, the host was kind of unpleasant and It just seemed no one was actually ready. My server tried to act professional but the atmosphere in the restaurant was not right. Food was so so and way too overpriced. I was really disappointed to find out another overrated restaurant in Baltimore.
Delicious food, great wine, excellent service.
Excellent service

My boyfriend took me here for my 29th birthday!!!! We ordered our 3 course ($30) and four course ($60) meals. Very decent prices. First time I tried duck and I loved it. In my opinion, duck is way better than steak. Although I was not a fan of the side of mushrooms in a balsamic reduction, everything else turned out fantastic. Not to mention their deserts are out of this world. Over all AMAZING food, great service and lovely atmosphere. I definitely will be a returning guest. I absolutely loved my experience! Cingahiale is an outstanding, one of a kind restaurant and I highly recommend making this place your next date night.
Amazing chacutteri made in-house
Perfect spot to grab a bite to eat when you’re flying solo for the night. Staff is very knowledgeable and pair things to perfection.
Got the 4 course meal and everything from the calamari to the perfectly seasoned and cooked veal was great.

Excellent food and wine, highly professional service, they really know their stuff. Leaving the place another guest was tipping the valet. He instantly gave it to a homeless man passing by. Thank you for being a good example!

Cinghiale was great. I went during restaurant week and didn't particularly love my dish, but our waiter was fantastic ( knowledgeable on the menu items and wine pairings) and the atmosphere was upscale. I will come back and give it another try based on that, alone.
Excellent service and food was tasty.
what is the best pasta dish that you have here?
Always a great meal and experience.  The Italian wine list is expansive and welll representative of the entire Country.
Great food
For the price, the food was ok. Nice looking restaurant. Great atmosphere and Superb service. Valet and coat check was provided. Overall good experience but the food should be worth the price....
Little bit of a wait during restaurant week but excellent food...
Very slow service.  Dinner took 2 hours.  Drink and water was also slow.  Food was good.
Best pappardelle I've had
Amazing food, impeccable service.  You cannot ask for a better dining atmosphere.
Free valet parking, pleasant space, menu that ventures beyond the typical Italian choices, slightly upscale. $200 for four before tip, with cocktails and appetizers but no desserts.

Went for restaurants week 2019. Had a fantastic salad, followed by mushroom cod, and panna cotta. Tuesday also happens to be half price wine night! The staff waa knowledgeable and friendly. I look forward to going back!

Had a fantastic dinner last night with my fiancé. We walked in on a whim and were warmly greeted by Andrew, the GM, who proceeded to make us feel like family.  Our server was excellent. Helpful and not overbearing.  The food was fantastic, from the appetizers (cheeses and grilled calamari), to the entrees (short rib and NY strip).  It goes without saying, but the atmosphere is perfect at Chingale as well.  Anyway....  Just go. It’s a restaurant done right.  Oh, and complimentary valet parking, they take your coats....  It’s how restaurants ought to be.
Small dishes
High class Italian cuisine
Yum!
Wonderful meal, friendly staff, and fantastic wine selection!
Great food and seriously good service.
Very good food, nice location. We had the calamari appetizer and grilled broccolini, super tasty. The saltimboca was also very good. I would definitely come again to try other dishes.
Good but pricey
Wonderful food, service and ambiance. I have never had such light and flavorful gnocchi...melted in your mouth!
Great food, wine and ambiance.
Great food, wine and service..A must go to place if in Baltimore
Wow! Totally unexpected dinner tonight! Everything was excellent from appetizers to dessert!

Had a casual business dinner here on a trip to visit an agency in Baltimore. I saw many Italian restaurants in searches and for unknown reasons chose here - what a great choice!  We had the fixed four course menu. All the dishes I had were unique and exquisite. First was a grilled calamari, second was a chestnut pasta (unbelievable!!) and third was venison loin that had the traditional dark cherry/berry sauce paired with a surprising spicy mustard that really made the dish stand out. I chose the dessert that was gelato with espresso poured over.  What a great meal!

I enjoyed my meal,  but it wasn't the same quality that i remember from this restaurant group.  I used to live in Baltimore and returned for a business trip.  Cinghiale's food is very good in the present,  but i remember it being exceptional, in the past. Service has remained excellent
My daughter and I went there... wow, great Italian wine list, fabulous pappardelle pasta and the service was magnificent!

I don’t typically eat Italian out. Seems like a waste of money. Cinghiale changed my mind. One of the best meals I can remember, and easily the best Italian I’ve had. Perfect preparation, great atmosphere, and our server was wonderful. Will definitely be back.

I ate at the bar.  Service was pleasant enough but they were clearly short staffed on this weekday evening.  It was hard to get any attention and orders were messed up.  The food was OK but not as good as I expected.
Great food and atmosphere!
Excellent food service and ambiance

Amazing restaurant! Food was great as always and the staff goes above and beyond to make sure everyone is happy with what they've ordered and that it is an enjoyable experience. Tuesday are 1/2 off wine bottles... great selection of wines.
A bit overpriced but the service was great.
(Translated by Google) Very good Attention and divine your meals ...  (Original) Muy buena Atención y divina sus comidas...
username: De todo un poco con Monica

caption: Amazing ambiance and staff.  Unique menu.  Listen to the staff recommendations.
Yummy

Chingale is one of our favorite places to eat. The food is always amazing, the flavor combinations they put together never disappoint. The staff is always friendly and engaging. The atmosphere is great. If you're looking for a nice night out, Chingale is your place. Make sure to try their risotto.

The food was bold but thoughtful. Radicchio salad was too much for me but the angel hair with beef ragu was melt in your mouth delicious. The duck was perfectly cooked at medium and the sauce was exactly what was needed. Dessert was panna cotta and gelato, not too heavy after a large meal but just what the taste buds needed to wrap up.
It's a over priced wine bar . Very fancy food ok, nice atmosphere.
The Italian capital in Baltimore!
Beautiful restaurant.
This place was amazing. We had a wonderful time. The bartender was awesome and the butcher was very knowledgeable and friendly. We will definitely be back here.
Cindy is still getting it done

We recently celebrated our anniversary with friends. Cinghiale has a beautiful rustic motiff with pretty views of the harbor. (Check out their signature bronze boars above the bar!!) They have complimentary valet parking, which makes it super easy to come and go. We shared two great bottles of wine, did a 3-course supper, and had charcuterie and cheese. The chef's choice for the cheese was good, but the meats were exceptional. Try the wild boar (Cinghiale) sausage! Detectable!
Wonderful restaurant and amazing staff
Awesome dinner, exceptional service!

Food was well prepared and tasty Restaurant week menu included 3 courses. The atmosphere was nice. Not thrilling but nice. Our waiter was attentive but condescending when I asked questions about wine choices. ( they are know for the wine cellar). I am not sure I would go back
Excellent food in the Inner Harbor. Great wine list and an incredibly knowledgeable staff. Great place to bring out of town guests.
Everything was great. Started with amazing bread, then delicious tomato soup, and fantastic fresh pasta!

This is one of my favorite restaurants in Baltimore right now. We've dined in both the formal dining room and the enoteca and enjoy the enoteca a lot more; you get the same level of service, but it feels a little more laid back. The menu consists of two prix fixe menus - a slightly smaller ~$30 option, and a full-blown $60+ option; however, you can also order dishes a la carte. Obviously pasta is going to be what a lot of people focus on for an Italian restaurant (and it is quite good) but don't sleep on some of the other options, including the charcuterie and the bronzino. I also recommend brushing up on your wine if you're so inclined, since the wine list is extensive. For the level of service and the quality of the food and drink, I think I Cinghiale is an absolute steal.
Wonderful experience. The wine pairing was terrific.
Great food! Great service! Good views.
Fantastic.  I've loved their food everyone I've been there!
Visited here for Restaurant Week 2018.  The atmosphere was very nice, the dining room was clean, and service was excellent.  I ordered the grilled Bronzino and it was excellent.

All my favorite places are Forman Wolf, and the food lived up to my expectations, exceptional. So much Barolo, Barbera, and Barbaresco. I was in foodie/wino heaven! Cheese for the last course, but cookies, too.
Excellent world class italian with a view!
Always perfect. The food and service is spectacular as all the Foreman Wolf restaurants offer. Consistent!
Freshly made pasta and an ever evolving menu with everything you would ever want in an Italian restaurant. Bravo times five!

Food is just not good. It's overpriced and undercooked. Pasta was hard around the edges and hardly warm. I don't understand how this place stays in business with such poor food quality. Amazing food, well made and authentic to Northern Italy. Accommodating of all dietary restrictions, even gluten on a menu with tons of pasta! all things can be made with a vegetarian stock, very little dairy is used as a staple in a dish, and the food is phenomenal. pasta is made fresh daily and the menu changes every day as well. the wine list is an extensive homage to Italian wine, moving through the entire country, region by region. Tuesdays are 12 price wine nights and you can try some stellar bottles that might be daunting at full price, but feel accessible at a discount (time to try that new wine that you don't know and not your tried and true) Amazing Salumeria which is charcuterie, and it is located between the 2 dining rooms so you can stop by and ask questions and taste a few things, it's encouraged! there are 2 pre fixe menu options so you can dine in courses and try something from each part of the menu. the nonna menu is 3 courses with classic dishes and a homey, family feel (it's literally grandma's menu) and the other is a 4 course menu that allows you to try some of the large plate options on the menu like the Hudson valley magret of duck or the crispy skin on rockfish, as well as a small portion of pasta, antipasti and dessert. Or you can order a la carte. great place to spend an evening and not just a fine dining establishment, the service will always be top notch, but it's accessible, just as great for a regular Tuesday night dinner as it is for an amazing anniversary celebration.
Upscale Italian dishes. Waitress was great along with the food. If you're looking for a nice date night, this is the place

While the many restaurants of Little Italy are great for having a great plate of spaghetti and meatballs and other Italian-American favorites, Cinghiale is the place to go in Baltimore for a more authentic Italian fare. Overlooking the harbor, you can dine on a variety of northern Italian specialties, charcuterie and opulent deserts in a very formal yet comfortable setting. Recommend the price set menu to get a full complement of the menu. Prices are higher than other places, but are on par with the neighborhood. Reservations are recommended; especially on weekend nights.
OMG!  That was amazing.

I dined at Cinghiale for the first time last night. The complimentary valet is extremely helpful and convenient. Ryan is the most amazing server. Everything about this dining experience was exquisite. The greeting, the delicious food, the wine pairings Ryan recommended, the presentation of the dishes, the quality of the meal- absolute perfection. I can't quite pick a favorite dish as each was outstanding but I especially loved the pheasant ravioli.
